race.comment: HEADBANGER (9) looks well placed off a let up. She's always had a bit of a profile without yet delivering, but she did run well when last seen at Cranbourne, getting into third there when backed into $2.35. She's won a jumpout in the interim and can look to deliver. Wary of BEL MEZYAAN (1) who debuts for the Jerome Hunter yard. He's a gelding by Mezyaan who looked good winning his latest trial here. He's drawn well and looks ready to go. LIFE AFTER LOVE (10) wasn't far away fresh over this trip at Sandown Lakeside and should be better for it. She ran in some good races last time in. ZUBBA STORM (5) has placed in all four runs to date and has to be considered again while TRAPPER JOHN (3) can run well on debut for the McDonald/Melham combination.
